        "timestamp": "2018-05-16 17:17:31.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 5: Code-Review-1\n\n> > Testing your patch with this one: https://gerrit.onap.org/r/#/c/44705/8,\n > > I see that the key for mysql is Values.geoEnabled yet in 44705,\n > the\n > > key is changed to Values.config.geoEnabled.\n > > Is this going to work as expected?\n > \n > mysql values is defining the key as Values.geoEnabled...\n\nAgreed that is the value key for the mysql chart.  My comment was asking which chart is setting this to true.  I don't see any chart that references this common/mysql chart ever setting mysql.geoEnabled=true so I question whether it works as expected.\n\nAssuming it is sdnc, then the sdnc charts values file needs to set that in the mysql: section where other mysql keys are overridden.",
